07:35.340 --> 07:39.640
And I wrote the book because I wanted people to benefit from my story,

07:39.800 --> 07:41.780
which is really my relationship with God.

07:41.780 --> 07:46.480
And I like people to think of it more as a relationship than as a religious book,

07:46.720 --> 07:48.580
and it's not, in fact, about that.

07:48.720 --> 07:54.500
I don't proselytize or try to convert people to a specific religion.

07:54.840 --> 08:00.640
My story started as a little boy where I was aware of the presence of God,

08:00.680 --> 08:05.880
and the presence of God that I was aware of was something I felt a need to develop.

08:05.880 --> 08:12.240
And I saw God as even a child as a creator God and a personal God,

08:12.320 --> 08:13.680
which meant I could communicate.

08:13.860 --> 08:20.360
So we opened with a little prayer, and I like to try to keep a continuous prayer idea with God

08:20.360 --> 08:22.140
where I'm always interacting.

08:22.300 --> 08:23.080
And there's an arena.

08:23.280 --> 08:26.880
The reason I entitled my book A State of Mind and Faith in the CIA

08:26.880 --> 08:30.960
was a state of mind refers to a desire to be close to God.

08:30.960 --> 08:35.280
John Paul II, it's a paraphrase of him saying,

08:35.900 --> 08:38.760
hell is not a place, which is an interesting concept.

08:38.900 --> 08:41.140
You figure Dante's Inferno, it's a state of mind.

08:41.460 --> 08:43.960
It's a state of mind of being separated from God.

08:45.260 --> 08:49.820
And throughout my life, I had a sort of a fear of being distant from God

08:49.820 --> 08:50.900
or not being close enough to God.

08:50.920 --> 08:53.260
But it wasn't a traditional thing of go to church and give money.

08:53.760 --> 08:56.420
It was more of like in my personal relationship with God,

08:56.480 --> 08:59.020
since God knows all things, God would be aware.

08:59.020 --> 09:03.960
And when I would pray in the way we started, I got responses

09:03.960 --> 09:07.500
and ultimately evolved into a destiny I felt.

09:07.580 --> 09:10.500
My destiny became tied to my relationship with God.

09:10.660 --> 09:16.260
My destiny was to fulfill God's wishes through my life and my experiences.

09:16.520 --> 09:20.920
And that set up certain conflicts with what I call my secular world of CIA,

09:21.580 --> 09:23.320
which I devoted my whole career to.

09:23.420 --> 09:25.080
Started in the military, went to West Point,

09:25.080 --> 09:30.360
and spent six years in the army at an auspicious time in the 70s

09:30.360 --> 09:33.240
on the Czech border, and then transferred over to CIA.

09:33.640 --> 09:39.640
So that whole story, all those experiences had their own role

09:39.640 --> 09:43.540
in national security, et cetera, but also in my relationship with God.

09:43.700 --> 09:48.280
And the faith part was understanding my faith as that relationship with God,

09:48.280 --> 09:52.760
not as what I called myself or what people thought of me in religious terms,

09:52.880 --> 09:56.200
but in my relationship with God, how was it developing?

09:56.640 --> 10:00.080
And was I fulfilling God's will through my actions and thoughts?

10:00.860 --> 10:05.320
And what did you end up doing at the CIA and throughout your intelligence career?

10:05.420 --> 10:08.620
I think a lot of people, what we try to do on the show is kind of marry

10:08.620 --> 10:13.400
some of the most out there experiences or claims people have

10:13.400 --> 10:16.500
with, you know, kind of rigorous credentials.

10:16.740 --> 10:18.400
Yeah, I think that's really important.

10:18.560 --> 10:24.160
So in my CIA career, I started as a, in Europe,

10:25.320 --> 10:27.560
just what we call a European officer.

10:27.760 --> 10:29.620
We had different areas of the world we were in.

10:29.700 --> 10:30.660
That was where I started.

10:30.820 --> 10:32.500
But I got quickly into arms control.

10:33.620 --> 10:36.160
And then over the years, I seemed to gravitate.

10:36.160 --> 10:39.840
I didn't think of this as things went on as being coincidental.

10:39.980 --> 10:42.840
It began to converge with my spiritual developments.

10:42.840 --> 10:47.680
More and more towards war and nuclear war, collapse of the Soviet Union.

10:47.960 --> 10:52.260
I did two tours in Moscow in the old days, in the Soviet days.

10:52.340 --> 10:53.000
I came back.

10:53.080 --> 10:55.100
I was what we call our chief of station in Moscow

10:55.100 --> 10:57.620
after the collapse of the Soviet Union.

10:59.020 --> 11:02.420
Of course, I hope that gives me some credibility on my religious,

11:02.800 --> 11:04.420
or my spiritual experiences.

11:04.420 --> 11:08.700
But they were, they were my credibility as an intelligence officer

11:08.700 --> 11:12.000
that I was always seem to be at the threshold of history.

11:12.000 --> 11:13.860
Like many, I'm not unique in that, by the way.

11:13.900 --> 11:17.500
There are so many of us that have been observers of history,

11:17.660 --> 11:19.960
helping to make history in some small way.

11:20.160 --> 11:22.280
And I was extremely fortunate in my career.

11:22.580 --> 11:26.260
Moscow ended my, or we did nine tours overseas,

11:26.260 --> 11:31.020
each two, three years under cover, sometimes deep cover,

11:31.160 --> 11:35.420
through the whole experience, and ended the whole thing,

11:35.420 --> 11:37.020
which I don't think was a coincidence,

11:37.020 --> 11:39.800
in the Middle East between 2011 and 16,

11:40.740 --> 11:44.820
when we served in the Middle East for the last five years.

11:44.920 --> 11:47.680
So between Europe, Soviet Union, Middle East,

11:47.900 --> 11:51.920
we sort of saw the whole world, served as CIA officers.

11:52.080 --> 11:54.300
My wife also worked most of that time in CIA.

11:54.560 --> 11:57.320
She's written her own book called Story of a CIA Wife.

11:57.320 --> 12:00.140
I'll close with one thing.

12:00.240 --> 12:01.760
I mean, people have different reactions.

12:01.880 --> 12:03.820
The first day I walked in CIA headquarters,

12:04.900 --> 12:06.360
you see the stars on the wall.

12:06.480 --> 12:08.160
It makes a huge, and if the stars on the wall

12:08.160 --> 12:10.360
are CIA officers who fall on the line of duty.

12:10.620 --> 12:12.180
They can't put their names to the star.

12:12.240 --> 12:15.340
There's a book that has that code book

12:15.340 --> 12:18.960
that tells you this star here is this person.

12:19.160 --> 12:20.500
There are people who lost their lives

12:20.500 --> 12:22.280
serving their country overseas.

12:22.280 --> 12:25.960
And, of course, I never wanted to be on that wall,

12:26.380 --> 12:27.200
like any of us.

12:27.560 --> 12:30.560
But right next to that, the stars on the wall,

12:30.660 --> 12:33.600
was this large, bold imprint

12:33.600 --> 12:36.560
into the marble walls of the CIA atrium

12:36.560 --> 12:38.060
when you walk inside the big building,

12:38.160 --> 12:39.940
the old headquarters in Virginia.

12:40.320 --> 12:42.580
And it says, John 832,

12:43.260 --> 12:44.520
you shall know the truth,

12:44.560 --> 12:45.860
and the truth shall set you free.

12:47.300 --> 12:49.900
And I thought, wow, this is really quite extraordinary

12:49.900 --> 12:52.780
that CIA, you know, secular organization,

12:53.500 --> 12:59.060
has this New Testament verse on the wall.

12:59.220 --> 13:00.480
And I wondered at the time

13:00.480 --> 13:01.640
when I walked in the building

13:01.640 --> 13:03.780
whether I would be satisfied

13:03.780 --> 13:05.360
that that's what CIA was all about.

13:05.440 --> 13:08.320
Were we truth seekers or not truth seekers?

13:08.580 --> 13:10.260
And that's the ultimate litmus test.

13:10.340 --> 13:11.420
When we don't seek truth

13:11.420 --> 13:12.440
and we have another agenda,

13:12.540 --> 13:15.780
we do bad things as CIA or intelligence officers

13:15.780 --> 13:17.380
or army officers or anything in life.

13:17.380 --> 13:19.020
Do you find that at times the CIA

13:19.020 --> 13:21.140
has not sought truth in the past?

13:21.140 --> 13:22.380
Oh, of course, of course.

13:22.540 --> 13:23.560
I mean, people are people,

13:23.680 --> 13:25.120
organizations are organizations.

13:25.500 --> 13:27.820
The problem with giving organizations

13:27.820 --> 13:30.460
such powers as CIA has

13:30.460 --> 13:33.020
is on the positive side,

13:33.080 --> 13:34.340
you can accomplish great things.

13:34.420 --> 13:35.200
On the negative side,

13:35.280 --> 13:36.660
you can do very bad things.

13:37.020 --> 13:39.040
And especially when you're doing them in secret.

13:39.500 --> 13:40.720
You have some interesting stories

13:40.720 --> 13:42.060
that you talk about in the book

13:42.060 --> 13:44.320
of being in the Oval Office,

13:44.320 --> 13:46.500
giving Bush advice,

13:46.720 --> 13:48.060
giving Cheney advice.

13:48.860 --> 13:51.560
Do you want to give a couple of examples there

13:51.560 --> 13:54.540
of just stories where you kind of helped out

13:54.540 --> 13:57.120
or advised in kind of very high up

13:57.120 --> 13:59.120
American national security contexts?

13:59.380 --> 13:59.400
Right.

13:59.880 --> 14:03.780
My career breaks down into three phases, really.

14:03.920 --> 14:05.640
The first phase was between

14:05.640 --> 14:09.620
when I started 1983 to 1991

14:09.620 --> 14:11.300
with the collapse of the Soviet Union.

14:11.660 --> 14:13.120
That's what we sometimes refer to

14:13.120 --> 14:14.000
as the good old days,

14:14.400 --> 14:16.320
which was espionage in the shadows,

14:16.960 --> 14:18.180
like the books you always read,

14:18.220 --> 14:19.560
the classic espionage books

14:19.560 --> 14:21.680
of running spies and great stuff.

14:21.800 --> 14:23.320
And I became really good at that.

14:23.400 --> 14:24.500
Then suddenly, boom,

14:25.380 --> 14:27.040
almost 10 years into my career,

14:27.240 --> 14:28.420
we get with almost exactly,

14:28.520 --> 14:29.480
we get hit with 9-11.

14:29.940 --> 14:31.160
And after 9-11,

14:31.420 --> 14:33.960
I was actually in language training

14:33.960 --> 14:35.240
to go to Asia to become

14:35.240 --> 14:36.040
the chief of station

14:36.040 --> 14:37.280
of a large Asian country

14:37.280 --> 14:39.080
when I saw on TV

14:39.080 --> 14:40.480
that the Twin Towers

14:40.480 --> 14:41.700
got hit by terrorists.

14:42.840 --> 14:44.260
I had been on the director,

14:44.400 --> 14:45.780
director of CIA staff

14:45.780 --> 14:47.820
the year before preceding 9-11

14:47.820 --> 14:49.940
as associate director

14:49.940 --> 14:50.900
of central intelligence

14:50.900 --> 14:52.120
for military support.

14:52.300 --> 14:53.460
So I was a staffer

14:53.460 --> 14:55.520
supporting the director,

14:55.680 --> 14:56.840
who was a good friend of mine,

14:56.900 --> 14:57.700
wonderful director,

14:57.780 --> 14:58.180
in my mind,

14:58.260 --> 14:58.800
George Tenet.

14:58.800 --> 15:00.980
And we knew that we were

15:00.980 --> 15:02.200
going to be hit 9-11.

15:03.760 --> 15:05.340
We didn't know where.

15:06.500 --> 15:09.580
And I'm not in the school of belief,

15:09.700 --> 15:11.100
and I know that it's a valid way

15:11.100 --> 15:11.640
to think of it,

15:11.680 --> 15:12.360
that we failed.

15:12.520 --> 15:13.440
Well, we failed because

15:13.440 --> 15:14.780
we allowed the attack to happen,

15:14.900 --> 15:16.600
but could we have prevented it?

15:16.660 --> 15:18.000
I think that's in ways

15:18.000 --> 15:20.340
a problematic way to think of it

15:20.340 --> 15:20.880
because I don't think

15:20.880 --> 15:22.460
we could have prevented 9-11.

15:22.960 --> 15:24.120
We just have to give the credit

15:24.120 --> 15:25.420
to the terrorists,

15:25.580 --> 15:26.720
to Osama bin Laden terrorists.

15:26.720 --> 15:28.340
But it changed everyone's lives

15:28.340 --> 15:29.360
and future of the world,

15:29.860 --> 15:30.940
and that was the intent

15:30.940 --> 15:31.560
of the terrorists,

15:31.660 --> 15:32.740
including my little life.

15:33.180 --> 15:33.900
So they pulled me

15:33.900 --> 15:34.980
from my language training,

15:35.100 --> 15:36.020
and George Tenet made me

15:36.020 --> 15:38.140
head of what they call

15:38.140 --> 15:39.600
the Weapons of Mass Destruction

15:39.600 --> 15:40.120
Department

15:40.120 --> 15:41.520
and the Counterterrorism Center,

15:41.760 --> 15:43.320
which was to stop terrorists

15:43.320 --> 15:44.700
from acquiring biological

15:44.700 --> 15:45.880
or nuclear weapons.

15:47.300 --> 15:48.600
I mean, that's a, yeah,

15:48.740 --> 15:51.480
if the future of the world

15:51.480 --> 15:52.760
hinges on any job,

15:52.860 --> 15:53.580
that's the job.

15:53.580 --> 15:55.800
I did say to George Tenet,

15:55.800 --> 15:56.760
who I already knew well

15:56.760 --> 15:57.220
because I'd been

15:57.220 --> 15:58.060
on his senior staff,

15:58.140 --> 15:58.800
I said, George,

15:59.320 --> 16:00.000
isn't there anybody

16:00.000 --> 16:01.760
better than me for this?

16:02.220 --> 16:02.900
How did he respond

16:02.900 --> 16:04.160
when he said, you know,

16:04.200 --> 16:05.060
hey, can't you find

16:05.060 --> 16:05.980
anybody better than me?

16:06.000 --> 16:07.300
Oh, classic George Tenet

16:07.300 --> 16:07.580
response.

16:07.900 --> 16:08.940
Like I said, great leader,

16:09.180 --> 16:10.540
a great leader of men and women.

16:10.920 --> 16:12.560
He said, hey,

16:12.680 --> 16:14.080
I got worse news for you.

16:14.080 --> 16:15.280
You don't have any people yet.

16:15.680 --> 16:17.060
I went from three people

16:17.060 --> 16:17.740
at that meeting

16:17.740 --> 16:19.360
that had been assigned to me

16:19.360 --> 16:21.760
to 150 over the next weeks.

16:22.100 --> 16:23.000
And then he said,

16:23.060 --> 16:24.880
but you were behind the eight ball,

16:24.880 --> 16:26.020
and he explained why,

16:26.120 --> 16:27.140
which is still classified,

16:27.360 --> 16:28.060
which meant there was

16:28.060 --> 16:29.580
a plausible reason

16:29.580 --> 16:30.240
to be worried

16:30.240 --> 16:31.800
that Al-Qaeda might obtain

16:31.800 --> 16:32.580
a nuclear weapon,

16:32.680 --> 16:33.100
which was,

16:33.460 --> 16:34.600
I can say the basics,

16:34.720 --> 16:36.260
which was they were negotiating

16:36.260 --> 16:38.440
with Pakistani nuclear scientists

16:38.440 --> 16:39.400
to try to acquire

16:39.400 --> 16:40.160
a nuclear weapon

16:40.160 --> 16:40.720
they could use

16:40.720 --> 16:41.460
in the United States.

16:42.680 --> 16:43.660
This was something,

16:43.860 --> 16:45.060
as George said to me,

16:45.460 --> 16:46.820
we can't fail on this.

16:47.480 --> 16:48.480
We're going to fail.

16:48.620 --> 16:49.980
We're like athletes

16:49.980 --> 16:50.940
playing in sports,

16:51.080 --> 16:51.600
team sports.

16:51.920 --> 16:52.920
Sometimes we fumble,

16:52.920 --> 16:54.600
sometimes the other team scores.

16:55.220 --> 16:57.100
We can't let them score on this.

16:57.180 --> 16:58.700
We can't let them do this one time

16:58.700 --> 16:59.760
and take out the White House

16:59.760 --> 17:00.920
or Congress or something.

17:01.660 --> 17:04.000
And so you're just going to have

17:04.000 --> 17:04.960
to make sure the president

17:04.960 --> 17:06.480
knows everything we know

17:06.480 --> 17:07.540
when we know it.

17:08.920 --> 17:10.840
We met as a group,

17:10.900 --> 17:12.120
and a lot of this is in my book,

17:12.160 --> 17:12.620
of course.

17:13.080 --> 17:14.940
We met every day at five o'clock,

17:14.980 --> 17:16.600
and we just pulled

17:16.600 --> 17:17.700
everything together raw.

17:17.940 --> 17:18.720
Nothing was going through

17:18.720 --> 17:19.680
the normal formats.

17:19.840 --> 17:20.680
All our information,

17:20.780 --> 17:21.680
we briefed the director,

17:21.680 --> 17:23.360
and when we had the meeting

17:23.360 --> 17:24.180
at five,

17:24.300 --> 17:25.120
it usually lasts

17:25.120 --> 17:26.180
till eight or nine at night.

17:27.340 --> 17:28.940
And just going around the table,

17:29.100 --> 17:30.160
everybody sharing everything

17:30.160 --> 17:31.160
they know with everybody,

17:31.240 --> 17:32.220
and everybody included,

17:32.400 --> 17:33.720
usually the FBI director,

17:33.960 --> 17:34.540
Robert Mueller,

17:35.420 --> 17:36.000
who, of course,

17:36.040 --> 17:37.340
I also got to know very well.

17:37.840 --> 17:39.020
The NSA director,

17:39.120 --> 17:39.760
Mike Hayden,

17:40.040 --> 17:41.520
was part of the group.

17:41.820 --> 17:43.160
And just a number of people

17:43.160 --> 17:44.400
around the Washington area

17:44.400 --> 17:45.180
who needed to know.

17:45.260 --> 17:46.100
Somebody would pop in

17:46.100 --> 17:47.660
from the National Security Council.

17:48.120 --> 17:48.760
Stephen Hadley,

17:48.920 --> 17:49.300
part of it.

17:49.300 --> 17:50.720
Stephen Hadley was often,

17:50.780 --> 17:51.160
you know,

17:51.260 --> 17:52.120
involved.

17:52.640 --> 17:53.980
And everything was briefed raw.

17:54.040 --> 17:54.840
The president was told

17:54.840 --> 17:55.680
everything that night.

17:55.800 --> 17:56.740
First thing in the morning,

17:57.300 --> 17:58.660
he was briefed by Bob Mueller

17:58.660 --> 17:59.720
and George Tenet together,

17:59.860 --> 18:01.240
the FBI and CIA directors.

18:01.820 --> 18:03.600
And then we would come in ad hoc.

18:03.920 --> 18:05.080
And I would go in,

18:05.180 --> 18:06.520
and I outlined some of the

18:06.520 --> 18:07.260
most important,

18:07.340 --> 18:07.680
you know,

18:07.840 --> 18:09.060
moments of briefing

18:09.060 --> 18:10.380
the president,

18:10.500 --> 18:11.180
when there was something

18:11.180 --> 18:11.820
extraordinary

18:11.820 --> 18:13.280
from my area.

18:13.280 --> 18:15.260
And I felt an immense

18:15.260 --> 18:15.900
responsibility.

18:16.340 --> 18:17.080
So the answer,

18:17.260 --> 18:17.820
the short answer

18:17.820 --> 18:18.740
to your question is,

18:19.420 --> 18:20.980
I would brief the president

18:20.980 --> 18:22.100
when there was a possibility

18:22.100 --> 18:22.820
we were going to get hit

18:22.820 --> 18:23.440
with a biological

18:23.440 --> 18:24.480
or nuclear attack

18:24.480 --> 18:25.380
because something

18:25.380 --> 18:26.060
was developing.

18:26.260 --> 18:27.420
And he needed to know

18:27.420 --> 18:28.260
because usually

18:28.260 --> 18:29.740
it was something

18:29.740 --> 18:30.500
that we couldn't,

18:30.780 --> 18:31.460
we didn't know

18:31.460 --> 18:32.520
exactly the timing

18:32.520 --> 18:33.220
and we weren't

18:33.220 --> 18:34.360
entirely sure

18:34.360 --> 18:36.960
of the accuracy

18:36.960 --> 18:37.920
or the providence

18:37.920 --> 18:38.860
of the threat.

18:38.860 --> 18:39.660
But we knew

18:39.660 --> 18:40.360
he needed to know

18:40.360 --> 18:41.320
because we don't want

18:41.320 --> 18:42.180
him to read about it

18:42.180 --> 18:42.920
with us

18:42.920 --> 18:43.740
when it happens.

18:44.900 --> 18:46.400
And for example,

18:46.600 --> 18:47.240
probably the most,

18:47.300 --> 18:47.720
the most,

18:47.760 --> 18:49.480
most important

18:49.480 --> 18:49.940
of the whole,

18:50.080 --> 18:51.200
of my whole experience

18:51.200 --> 18:51.860
with the president

18:51.860 --> 18:53.040
was when I briefed him

18:53.040 --> 18:54.760
that right three weeks

18:54.760 --> 18:56.160
before we invaded Iraq.

18:56.480 --> 18:57.200
So now we're talking

18:57.200 --> 18:58.020
2003.

18:59.900 --> 19:01.540
We obtained information

19:01.540 --> 19:03.840
that a notorious terrorist

19:03.840 --> 19:04.660
that my people

19:04.660 --> 19:05.320
were tracking,

19:05.880 --> 19:06.360
his name was

19:06.360 --> 19:07.680
Abu Musab al-Zarqawi.

19:07.680 --> 19:08.540
He's a famous

19:08.540 --> 19:09.500
jihadist.

19:09.560 --> 19:10.380
He was head of Al-Qaeda

19:10.380 --> 19:10.960
in Iraq

19:10.960 --> 19:12.700
once we,

19:12.940 --> 19:13.220
later.

19:13.980 --> 19:14.900
But this is before

19:14.900 --> 19:15.520
the invasion.

19:16.100 --> 19:16.940
So this information

19:16.940 --> 19:17.860
is very privileged

19:17.860 --> 19:18.520
at the time.

19:18.920 --> 19:20.020
And I had briefed

19:20.020 --> 19:20.400
the president

19:20.400 --> 19:21.060
several times

19:21.060 --> 19:22.020
on him and his network

19:22.020 --> 19:22.740
and how they were

19:22.740 --> 19:23.320
trying to obtain

19:23.320 --> 19:23.920
these weapons.

19:24.660 --> 19:25.580
And I came in,

19:25.620 --> 19:25.820
I said,

19:25.860 --> 19:26.260
Mr. President,

19:26.300 --> 19:27.080
I have bad news.

19:27.540 --> 19:28.080
The only people

19:28.080 --> 19:28.760
in the Oval Office

19:28.760 --> 19:29.220
were me,

19:29.320 --> 19:29.840
George Tenet,

19:30.980 --> 19:32.880
and George Bush,

19:33.280 --> 19:34.140
George H.W. Bush.

19:35.300 --> 19:36.280
He was in a wheelchair

19:36.280 --> 19:36.860
at the time.

19:36.860 --> 19:37.940
So it was an amazing

19:37.940 --> 19:38.460
sight for me

19:38.460 --> 19:38.960
as a citizen.

19:39.180 --> 19:40.120
And I have to say

19:40.120 --> 19:40.760
to your listeners,

19:40.980 --> 19:41.100
you know,

19:41.100 --> 19:44.200
W and his father

19:44.200 --> 19:44.840
and George

19:44.840 --> 19:45.180
and me,

19:45.240 --> 19:45.640
that was it

19:45.640 --> 19:46.280
in the Oval Office

19:46.280 --> 19:47.340
for an hour.

19:47.740 --> 19:47.880
Wow.

19:48.940 --> 19:50.480
And I have to tell you

19:50.480 --> 19:50.880
as an American,

19:50.980 --> 19:51.500
I had goosebumps.

19:52.500 --> 19:52.900
Yeah.

19:53.160 --> 19:53.360
Yeah.

19:53.420 --> 19:54.100
And everything

19:54.100 --> 19:54.600
I had briefed

19:54.600 --> 19:55.080
the president,

19:55.340 --> 19:55.620
you know,

19:55.740 --> 19:56.960
all I had

19:56.960 --> 19:57.560
from dealing

19:57.560 --> 19:58.000
with everybody

19:58.000 --> 19:58.500
I dealt with

19:58.500 --> 19:59.000
at that level

19:59.000 --> 20:00.240
was they were

20:00.240 --> 20:01.680
incredibly dedicated

20:01.680 --> 20:02.880
to serving this country.

20:02.980 --> 20:03.580
They were incredibly

20:03.580 --> 20:04.500
dedicated to doing

20:04.500 --> 20:05.000
the right thing.

20:05.000 --> 20:05.520
all the things

20:05.520 --> 20:06.000
you hear.

20:06.540 --> 20:07.000
And the president

20:07.000 --> 20:07.780
is very smart.

20:07.980 --> 20:08.880
He remembered

20:08.880 --> 20:09.940
everything from the previous,

20:10.000 --> 20:10.360
I don't even know

20:10.360 --> 20:10.860
how he did it,

20:10.880 --> 20:11.180
frankly.

20:11.780 --> 20:12.580
He would recall

20:12.580 --> 20:13.120
the facts

20:13.120 --> 20:13.900
of the previous time

20:13.900 --> 20:14.480
I talked to him

20:14.480 --> 20:15.380
if it was a month earlier

20:15.380 --> 20:15.940
or two months

20:15.940 --> 20:16.260
or whatever,

20:16.360 --> 20:17.120
he'd remember.

20:17.660 --> 20:18.460
So this time

20:18.460 --> 20:19.120
I told him,

20:19.400 --> 20:20.620
we know where he is.

20:20.680 --> 20:21.700
He's in this camp

20:21.700 --> 20:22.660
in northeast Iraq.

20:22.780 --> 20:23.060
Now remember,

20:23.160 --> 20:23.820
this is three weeks

20:23.820 --> 20:25.060
before we invaded Iraq.

20:26.060 --> 20:27.400
So I said

20:27.400 --> 20:28.200
to the president,

20:28.520 --> 20:29.280
he's here

20:29.280 --> 20:29.580
and I had

20:29.580 --> 20:30.420
the overhead imagery

20:30.420 --> 20:31.700
of the camp

20:31.700 --> 20:32.940
and I had

20:32.940 --> 20:34.680
a nominated board

20:34.680 --> 20:35.300
with all the

20:35.300 --> 20:36.240
jihadist terrorists

20:36.240 --> 20:36.940
that were working

20:36.940 --> 20:37.200
with him

20:37.200 --> 20:37.880
and him on the top.

20:38.060 --> 20:38.500
His picture,

20:38.580 --> 20:38.900
his mug.

20:40.120 --> 20:41.020
And the president

20:41.020 --> 20:41.760
who already knew him

20:41.760 --> 20:41.900
well,

20:41.940 --> 20:42.340
he said,

20:42.840 --> 20:43.060
Rolf,

20:43.080 --> 20:43.680
what would you do

20:43.680 --> 20:44.660
if you were me?

20:46.640 --> 20:47.040
Now,

20:47.180 --> 20:47.860
when I briefed

20:47.860 --> 20:48.380
the president,

20:49.040 --> 20:49.740
I hope this is

20:49.740 --> 20:50.660
reassuring to

20:50.660 --> 20:51.520
your listeners

20:51.520 --> 20:52.500
as I tried to make it,

20:53.140 --> 20:54.000
I did it as a,

20:54.000 --> 20:55.320
I did it as a citizen,

20:55.500 --> 20:56.500
like I'm not putting

20:56.500 --> 20:57.420
any of my spin

20:57.420 --> 20:57.920
or influence

20:57.920 --> 20:58.360
on anything

20:58.360 --> 20:59.160
I'm telling the president.

20:59.380 --> 21:00.420
There's no Rolf agenda.

21:01.080 --> 21:02.360
That was my key test.

21:02.460 --> 21:03.140
I had facts,

21:03.240 --> 21:04.220
I had things to say,

21:04.520 --> 21:05.820
I never went beyond the,

21:06.140 --> 21:06.840
and that day

21:06.840 --> 21:07.240
we had had

21:07.240 --> 21:08.220
an internal discussion

21:08.220 --> 21:09.420
on exactly what I should say

21:09.420 --> 21:09.960
to the president

21:09.960 --> 21:11.360
about what I'm describing,

21:11.980 --> 21:12.600
including that

21:12.600 --> 21:13.600
we shouldn't do anything.

21:13.700 --> 21:14.780
We should let this play out

21:14.780 --> 21:15.540
and I was too close

21:15.540 --> 21:16.220
to the invasion.

21:18.020 --> 21:18.940
But when he looked at me

21:18.940 --> 21:19.360
and he said that

21:19.360 --> 21:20.220
I started to say

21:20.220 --> 21:22.000
what I was told to say

21:22.000 --> 21:23.880
and he knew me too well

21:23.880 --> 21:24.400
so he said,

21:24.500 --> 21:24.600
look,

21:24.700 --> 21:26.540
I don't want to know

21:26.540 --> 21:27.360
what they are telling you

21:27.360 --> 21:27.840
to tell me.

21:27.980 --> 21:28.760
What do you think

21:28.760 --> 21:29.420
I should do?

21:29.540 --> 21:30.520
What were you told to say?

21:30.720 --> 21:31.540
I was told to say

21:31.540 --> 21:32.840
we shouldn't bomb it,

21:32.880 --> 21:33.860
we shouldn't attack it

21:33.860 --> 21:35.460
because it could,

21:35.660 --> 21:35.920
you know,

21:35.960 --> 21:36.500
the invasion

21:36.500 --> 21:37.720
and I was already,

21:37.840 --> 21:38.740
because I was obsessed

21:38.740 --> 21:40.640
with this terrorist.

21:40.840 --> 21:41.460
I was obsessed

21:41.460 --> 21:42.320
and I knew that

21:42.320 --> 21:43.800
it was an unhealthy obsession.

21:44.340 --> 21:44.980
I had been known

21:44.980 --> 21:46.160
to be slightly obsessive

21:46.160 --> 21:47.240
in work,

21:47.440 --> 21:47.740
you know,

21:47.880 --> 21:48.820
hopefully not other things.

21:49.360 --> 21:50.280
But it turned out

21:50.280 --> 21:50.620
that,

21:50.620 --> 21:51.940
you know,

21:52.220 --> 21:53.380
my look betrayed

21:53.380 --> 21:54.720
because I was so zealously

21:54.720 --> 21:55.360
telling him,

21:55.820 --> 21:56.440
here he is,

21:56.500 --> 21:57.220
here they are.

21:57.640 --> 21:57.860
He says,

21:57.900 --> 21:57.980
no,

21:58.040 --> 21:58.260
I mean,

21:58.300 --> 21:58.760
what would you do

21:58.760 --> 21:59.380
if you were me?

21:59.720 --> 22:00.360
You're telling me

22:00.360 --> 22:00.980
not to do anything

22:00.980 --> 22:01.520
but you're saying

22:01.520 --> 22:02.620
something else.

22:02.660 --> 22:03.100
I think you're

22:03.100 --> 22:04.660
thinking something else.

22:05.400 --> 22:06.620
So I looked at the director

22:06.620 --> 22:07.820
and he just gave me the,

22:08.600 --> 22:08.840
like,

22:08.980 --> 22:09.960
he asked you the question.

22:10.420 --> 22:11.820
He didn't ask me the question,

22:11.880 --> 22:12.640
he asked you the question,

22:12.700 --> 22:13.520
you answer the question.

22:13.520 --> 22:16.780
And I looked at the director,

22:16.880 --> 22:17.580
looked back at the president

22:17.580 --> 22:17.920
and I said,

22:17.960 --> 22:18.380
Mr. President,

22:18.420 --> 22:19.020
I'd bomb it.

22:20.900 --> 22:22.040
So nobody said anything.

22:22.120 --> 22:23.060
He just went on a meeting.

22:23.160 --> 22:24.940
He didn't seem nonplussed

22:24.940 --> 22:25.640
by the whole thing or anything.

22:25.820 --> 22:26.760
We're driving back

22:26.760 --> 22:27.760
in the director's car

22:27.760 --> 22:29.440
to this agency headquarters

22:29.440 --> 22:30.160
and he says,

22:30.860 --> 22:31.420
well,

22:32.460 --> 22:32.680
oh,

22:32.700 --> 22:33.380
I said to him,

22:33.560 --> 22:33.740
well,

22:33.780 --> 22:35.000
should I have said that?

22:36.000 --> 22:36.320
He goes,

22:36.400 --> 22:37.180
he asked you,

22:37.300 --> 22:38.020
you told him,

22:38.220 --> 22:39.380
I have no problem with it.

22:39.540 --> 22:39.900
He goes,

22:40.060 --> 22:40.700
typical.

22:41.240 --> 22:42.140
Now when you get back

22:42.140 --> 22:43.060
to our building,

22:43.060 --> 22:43.840
you make sure you tell

22:43.840 --> 22:44.720
everybody what you said.

22:45.960 --> 22:46.380
And of course,

22:46.520 --> 22:47.940
there's no,

22:48.280 --> 22:49.540
one thing I liked,

22:49.720 --> 22:50.800
I think I emphasized

22:50.800 --> 22:51.660
in my book,

22:52.440 --> 22:54.480
the right and the wrong

22:54.480 --> 22:55.320
and who's to blame

22:55.320 --> 22:57.340
is so much less

22:57.340 --> 22:58.100
on our minds

22:58.100 --> 22:59.080
when we're doing things

22:59.080 --> 23:00.300
than people think it is.

23:00.420 --> 23:00.580
Like,

23:00.620 --> 23:01.660
we're just trying to make,

23:01.840 --> 23:02.680
do the right thing.

23:03.240 --> 23:04.580
And sometimes we do

23:04.580 --> 23:05.840
and sometimes we don't.

23:06.900 --> 23:08.220
Speaking of this

23:08.220 --> 23:09.280
pivotal moment

23:09.280 --> 23:10.820
and at least

23:10.820 --> 23:11.380
from the

23:11.380 --> 23:12.860
kind of public

23:12.860 --> 23:13.540
perception,

23:14.100 --> 23:14.440
you know,

23:14.780 --> 23:16.040
intelligence failure

23:16.040 --> 23:16.720
or wrongdoing,

23:16.920 --> 23:17.620
people think of the

23:17.620 --> 23:19.360
overall invasion

23:19.360 --> 23:20.420
of Iraq,

23:20.580 --> 23:21.320
which is not,

23:21.580 --> 23:21.860
you know,

23:21.940 --> 23:23.140
for the audience

23:23.140 --> 23:23.840
at all what you're

23:23.840 --> 23:24.240
talking about

23:24.240 --> 23:24.800
with this targeted

23:24.800 --> 23:25.700
bombing of Zarqawi.

23:26.280 --> 23:27.080
They think of that

23:27.080 --> 23:28.120
as an intelligence failure

23:28.120 --> 23:29.260
because they think of

23:29.260 --> 23:31.320
us as having tagged

23:31.320 --> 23:32.780
Saddam Hussein

23:32.780 --> 23:34.320
with weapons

23:34.320 --> 23:35.160
of mass destruction

23:35.160 --> 23:36.500
when he never had any.

23:36.640 --> 23:36.700
And,

23:36.820 --> 23:36.940
you know,

23:36.960 --> 23:37.580
maybe at most

23:37.580 --> 23:38.180
he used,

23:38.180 --> 23:38.940
you know,

23:39.140 --> 23:40.700
biological weapons

23:40.700 --> 23:41.200
in Kuwait,

23:41.280 --> 23:41.820
which is horrible

23:41.820 --> 23:42.240
and he was,

23:42.340 --> 23:42.480
you know,

23:42.500 --> 23:43.300
a very bad guy.

23:43.840 --> 23:44.120
But,

23:44.200 --> 23:44.540
you know,

23:44.560 --> 23:45.140
maybe this was

23:45.140 --> 23:45.820
this kind of,

23:45.880 --> 23:46.300
you know,

23:46.300 --> 23:49.760
huge waste of money,

23:49.980 --> 23:50.520
you know,

23:50.580 --> 23:51.980
lives and,

23:52.080 --> 23:52.200
you know,

23:52.260 --> 23:53.360
created this kind of

23:53.360 --> 23:54.700
void or vacuum

23:54.700 --> 23:56.940
for which ISIS,

23:57.420 --> 23:57.600
you know,

23:57.660 --> 23:58.140
ironically,

23:58.380 --> 23:59.180
to actually like

23:59.180 --> 23:59.840
take root

23:59.840 --> 24:00.580
and,

24:00.640 --> 24:01.000
you know,

24:01.000 --> 24:01.760
which kind of ended up

24:01.760 --> 24:02.700
radicalizing the region

24:02.700 --> 24:03.140
even more.

24:03.260 --> 24:03.380
So,

24:03.700 --> 24:03.840
yeah,

24:03.880 --> 24:04.800
I'm sure you were

24:04.800 --> 24:06.100
thinking deeply

24:06.100 --> 24:06.840
about this

24:06.840 --> 24:07.400
at the time.

24:07.900 --> 24:08.640
What do you think

24:08.640 --> 24:09.220
happened there?

24:09.720 --> 24:10.660
I struggled with

24:10.660 --> 24:11.220
whether I should

24:11.220 --> 24:11.760
include this,

24:11.840 --> 24:13.360
but I consider resigning

24:13.360 --> 24:15.040
when we invaded Iraq.

24:15.120 --> 24:15.400
Really?

24:15.540 --> 24:16.660
I noted that

24:16.660 --> 24:17.700
briefly.

24:17.920 --> 24:19.160
I didn't get into it

24:19.160 --> 24:19.740
in any detail.

24:19.740 --> 24:20.660
So you were against it?

24:20.820 --> 24:21.900
I was against the war

24:21.900 --> 24:22.740
philosophically,

24:22.880 --> 24:24.540
but some of my colleagues

24:24.540 --> 24:26.020
were also feeling

24:26.020 --> 24:26.500
it was going to be

24:26.500 --> 24:26.980
a disaster.

24:27.560 --> 24:28.540
The idea that

24:28.540 --> 24:29.320
we didn't know

24:29.320 --> 24:30.640
that it would

24:30.640 --> 24:31.460
turn out badly,

24:31.660 --> 24:32.560
I think most people

24:32.560 --> 24:33.040
who had the most

24:33.040 --> 24:33.880
experience knew

24:33.880 --> 24:34.380
this was going

24:34.380 --> 24:35.180
to turn out badly.

24:35.180 --> 24:37.480
Now the decision

24:37.480 --> 24:38.520
to do it,

24:38.580 --> 24:40.180
at least I believe,

24:40.360 --> 24:41.060
and I can't say,

24:41.200 --> 24:42.120
there's a lot of,

24:42.200 --> 24:43.100
there's a split decision

24:43.100 --> 24:44.240
of views on this.

24:44.780 --> 24:46.620
I don't see any

24:46.620 --> 24:49.000
intent for the administration

24:49.000 --> 24:50.360
to deceive anybody

24:50.360 --> 24:51.580
that by saying

24:51.580 --> 24:53.620
Saddam had WMD

24:53.620 --> 24:54.240
and he didn't.

24:54.720 --> 24:55.840
It was a failure,

24:56.120 --> 24:57.080
a massive failure

24:57.080 --> 24:59.200
to conclude that

24:59.200 --> 25:00.260
it was based

25:00.260 --> 25:01.200
on bad sources,

25:01.340 --> 25:01.940
which is usually

25:01.940 --> 25:03.080
the origin

25:03.080 --> 25:04.380
of all bad decisions

25:04.380 --> 25:05.060
in intelligence

25:05.060 --> 25:05.820
when you have

25:05.820 --> 25:07.440
dubious sources

25:07.440 --> 25:08.320
or bad sources.

25:08.660 --> 25:09.380
These were both

25:09.380 --> 25:10.280
sources that didn't

25:10.280 --> 25:10.740
know much

25:10.740 --> 25:12.160
and were over-representing

25:12.160 --> 25:12.840
and fabricating

25:12.840 --> 25:13.400
information,

25:13.500 --> 25:13.940
we call it,

25:13.980 --> 25:14.460
when you're making

25:14.460 --> 25:15.280
up information.

25:15.480 --> 25:16.460
And on that basis,

25:16.460 --> 25:17.260
we made a terrible

25:17.260 --> 25:17.820
decision,

25:18.160 --> 25:18.920
is my view.

25:19.640 --> 25:21.160
But it was exacerbated

25:21.160 --> 25:21.840
by the idea

25:21.840 --> 25:23.180
that even if it had

25:23.180 --> 25:24.040
been the right decision,

25:24.280 --> 25:25.400
the result probably

25:25.400 --> 25:25.760
would have been

25:25.760 --> 25:26.580
the same because

25:26.580 --> 25:28.260
we couldn't control Iraq

25:28.260 --> 25:28.840
like we couldn't

25:28.840 --> 25:29.700
control Afghanistan.

25:29.700 --> 25:31.360
and it didn't take,

25:32.040 --> 25:32.960
and I have a chapter

25:32.960 --> 25:33.440
in my book

25:33.440 --> 25:33.980
where I'm talking

25:33.980 --> 25:34.860
to the vice president,

25:35.000 --> 25:35.460
Dick Cheney,

25:35.500 --> 25:35.860
who I got done

25:35.860 --> 25:36.820
exceptionally well

25:36.820 --> 25:37.580
also,

25:38.100 --> 25:39.100
where he just called

25:39.100 --> 25:40.280
me in a weekend

25:40.280 --> 25:42.340
from the White House

25:42.340 --> 25:43.240
and I came in

25:43.240 --> 25:44.040
on a Sunday

25:44.040 --> 25:45.240
to talk to him

25:45.240 --> 25:46.060
about why are we

25:46.060 --> 25:46.980
losing the war

25:46.980 --> 25:48.020
by the summer

25:48.020 --> 25:48.900
of 2003.

25:49.340 --> 25:50.100
This is six months

25:50.100 --> 25:50.960
after our invasion.

25:51.280 --> 25:52.160
But I didn't say

25:52.160 --> 25:52.680
what I was really

25:52.680 --> 25:53.280
thinking was,

25:53.640 --> 25:53.920
you know,

25:54.080 --> 25:54.940
sorry Dick,

25:55.040 --> 25:55.480
but if you don't

25:55.480 --> 25:56.000
know what's going

25:56.000 --> 25:56.500
on here,

25:56.680 --> 25:57.820
I can't help you.

25:57.860 --> 25:58.640
And then I was

25:58.640 --> 25:59.380
really like worried

25:59.380 --> 25:59.940
that we didn't

25:59.940 --> 26:00.580
seem to know

26:00.580 --> 26:02.060
what we were up

26:02.060 --> 26:02.460
against.

26:02.720 --> 26:03.380
And that was

26:03.380 --> 26:04.960
the real shocker

26:04.960 --> 26:06.000
to me of Iraq

26:06.000 --> 26:06.680
wasn't that we

26:06.680 --> 26:07.460
made a mistake

26:07.460 --> 26:08.160
in the invasion

26:08.160 --> 26:08.780
side,

26:09.060 --> 26:10.120
as bad as that was,

26:10.400 --> 26:11.220
is that we didn't

26:11.220 --> 26:11.580
know what we were

26:11.580 --> 26:12.280
getting into.

26:13.400 --> 26:14.480
What's the most

26:14.480 --> 26:15.620
on the brink

26:15.620 --> 26:16.900
the world has been

26:16.900 --> 26:18.220
that you can

26:18.220 --> 26:18.860
talk about?

26:20.360 --> 26:20.400
Well,

26:20.800 --> 26:21.760
you know,

26:21.880 --> 26:23.140
the Soviet Union

26:23.140 --> 26:24.680
had collapsed

26:24.680 --> 26:27.400
and the biggest

26:27.400 --> 26:28.480
worry in Congress

26:28.480 --> 26:29.360
and in Washington's

26:29.360 --> 26:29.680
mind,

26:29.780 --> 26:30.500
which we had

26:30.500 --> 26:31.520
almost no inkling

26:31.520 --> 26:32.340
of in Moscow

26:32.340 --> 26:32.760
where we were

26:32.760 --> 26:33.180
actually doing

26:33.180 --> 26:33.520
the work,

26:34.120 --> 26:34.760
was that one

26:34.760 --> 26:35.260
of these nukes

26:35.260 --> 26:35.780
would end up

26:35.780 --> 26:37.160
in rogue states

26:37.160 --> 26:37.740
or terrorists.

26:38.420 --> 26:39.220
And the U.S.

26:39.300 --> 26:39.960
government at that

26:39.960 --> 26:40.660
time launched

26:40.660 --> 26:41.360
a heroic,

26:41.520 --> 26:42.180
really heroic

26:42.180 --> 26:43.180
effort with the

26:43.180 --> 26:44.940
Russians to try

26:44.940 --> 26:45.500
to account for

26:45.500 --> 26:46.360
every nuclear weapon.

26:46.900 --> 26:48.200
the so-called

26:48.200 --> 26:49.280
suitcase nukes.

26:50.080 --> 26:50.520
Nukes aren't

26:50.520 --> 26:51.100
just missiles

26:51.100 --> 26:51.940
that come in

26:51.940 --> 26:52.580
and destroy the

26:52.580 --> 26:52.800
world.

26:52.900 --> 26:53.380
That's really

26:53.380 --> 26:53.740
the answer

26:53.740 --> 26:54.200
to your question.

26:54.280 --> 26:54.900
My biggest worry

26:54.900 --> 26:55.320
was the world

26:55.320 --> 26:55.940
would blow up,

26:56.000 --> 26:56.260
literally.

26:57.020 --> 26:57.640
There's nothing

26:57.640 --> 26:58.380
fun about trying

26:58.380 --> 26:58.800
to stop

26:58.800 --> 26:59.580
terrorists with nukes.

26:59.860 --> 27:00.340
There's certainly

27:00.340 --> 27:01.160
nothing fun about

27:01.160 --> 27:02.020
trying to recover

27:02.020 --> 27:03.820
nukes in a country

27:03.820 --> 27:05.080
that's just lost

27:05.080 --> 27:05.920
control of its

27:05.920 --> 27:06.760
entire empire,

27:06.960 --> 27:07.820
like Russia had

27:07.820 --> 27:08.460
in 1991,

27:08.820 --> 27:09.300
2, and 3.

27:09.720 --> 27:10.880
So I'd say

27:10.880 --> 27:11.320
that answers

27:11.320 --> 27:11.960
two things.

27:12.040 --> 27:12.420
It answers

27:12.420 --> 27:13.060
kind of what

27:13.060 --> 27:13.480
the big,

27:14.580 --> 27:15.280
there are a lot

27:15.280 --> 27:15.960
of things to worry

27:15.960 --> 27:16.680
about in the world.

27:17.160 --> 27:17.380
You know,

27:17.460 --> 27:19.740
there's biotechnology,

27:20.260 --> 27:21.000
there's AI,

27:21.540 --> 27:22.120
there's nuclear,

27:22.200 --> 27:23.040
but nuclear weapons

27:23.040 --> 27:23.520
are still,

27:23.680 --> 27:23.940
for me,

27:24.020 --> 27:26.120
the king of the hill

27:26.120 --> 27:27.340
because it can

27:27.340 --> 27:28.340
happen that fast

27:28.340 --> 27:29.240
and we won't even

27:29.240 --> 27:29.880
be aware of it

27:29.880 --> 27:30.300
if we're not

27:30.300 --> 27:30.920
really serious

27:30.920 --> 27:31.540
about stopping

27:31.540 --> 27:32.260
it from happening.

27:32.260 --> 27:32.780
Yeah.

27:33.460 --> 27:34.140
Yeah, I mean,

27:34.180 --> 27:34.980
we're in a scary

27:34.980 --> 27:35.800
world right now

27:35.800 --> 27:36.540
where you have

27:36.540 --> 27:37.340
all these kind of,

27:37.340 --> 27:37.580
you know,

27:37.620 --> 27:38.360
this asymmetric

27:38.360 --> 27:39.480
warfare and all

27:39.480 --> 27:40.260
these capabilities

27:40.260 --> 27:41.420
and then all

27:41.420 --> 27:42.900
this ability

27:42.900 --> 27:44.240
for if you're

27:44.240 --> 27:45.220
China or Russia

27:45.220 --> 27:46.020
or some sort

27:46.020 --> 27:47.020
of larger adversary

27:47.020 --> 27:48.400
to gain plausible

27:48.400 --> 27:49.360
deniability and

27:49.360 --> 27:50.280
act through

27:50.280 --> 27:51.260
sort of rogue

27:51.260 --> 27:52.060
actors.

27:52.560 --> 27:53.600
But I want

27:53.600 --> 27:54.280
to back up

27:54.280 --> 27:55.200
and just talk

27:55.200 --> 27:56.660
about you've

27:56.660 --> 27:57.360
had these kind

27:57.360 --> 27:57.920
of mystical

27:57.920 --> 27:59.560
downloads and I

27:59.560 --> 27:59.920
want to talk

27:59.920 --> 28:00.460
about the first

28:00.460 --> 28:00.840
one.

28:01.040 --> 28:01.860
You were kind

28:01.860 --> 28:03.080
of a nihilistic

28:03.080 --> 28:04.640
youth at West

28:04.640 --> 28:04.960
Point.

28:05.180 --> 28:05.380
Yeah.

28:05.460 --> 28:06.040
What happened?

28:07.020 --> 28:07.840
Well, you know,

28:07.880 --> 28:08.920
there was a

28:08.920 --> 28:11.040
point in my life

28:11.040 --> 28:11.720
when I was,

28:13.140 --> 28:14.540
I combined my

28:14.540 --> 28:15.220
interest in

28:15.220 --> 28:16.120
knowing truth

28:16.120 --> 28:17.280
and to an

28:17.280 --> 28:18.080
extreme where I

28:18.080 --> 28:18.840
was receptive

28:18.840 --> 28:20.880
to whatever

28:20.880 --> 28:22.360
input I would

28:22.360 --> 28:22.960
get to the

28:22.960 --> 28:23.500
point I pushed

28:23.500 --> 28:25.120
myself to an

28:25.120 --> 28:25.560
extreme.

28:25.820 --> 28:26.960
I had had

28:26.960 --> 28:28.880
experiences where

28:28.880 --> 28:29.880
I had dreams that

28:29.920 --> 28:31.060
came true and

28:31.060 --> 28:32.700
I realized that I

28:32.700 --> 28:33.280
started thinking

28:33.280 --> 28:34.400
about consciousness

28:34.400 --> 28:35.720
and subconsciousness

28:35.720 --> 28:36.440
and these were

28:36.440 --> 28:37.040
things that were

28:37.040 --> 28:37.900
affecting me in

28:37.900 --> 28:39.100
terms of being

28:39.100 --> 28:39.980
receptive to the

28:39.980 --> 28:40.680
idea that there's

28:40.680 --> 28:41.480
way more out there

28:41.480 --> 28:42.220
than we see in

28:42.220 --> 28:42.940
logic and reason

28:42.940 --> 28:43.500
or even if you

28:43.500 --> 28:44.400
add intuition to

28:44.400 --> 28:44.880
that, right?

28:45.340 --> 28:45.980
And so at West

28:45.980 --> 28:46.980
Point, I did these

28:46.980 --> 28:47.760
dream experiences.

28:47.760 --> 28:48.420
I talk a little

28:48.420 --> 28:48.880
bit out of the

28:48.880 --> 28:49.040
book.

28:49.120 --> 28:49.580
They were kind

28:49.580 --> 28:50.600
of childish in

28:50.600 --> 28:51.200
a way and not

28:51.200 --> 28:52.200
very scientific.

28:52.760 --> 28:53.520
But then when I

28:53.520 --> 28:55.580
graduated, I went

28:55.580 --> 28:56.860
to Fort Knox as

28:56.860 --> 28:57.560
an armor officer.

28:57.660 --> 28:57.980
I was going to go

28:57.980 --> 28:58.380
to the Czech

28:58.380 --> 28:59.660
border as an

28:59.660 --> 29:01.960
arms guy and

29:01.960 --> 29:04.260
they started to

29:04.260 --> 29:05.300
become much more

29:05.300 --> 29:06.440
vivid and the

29:06.440 --> 29:07.660
first briefing I

29:07.660 --> 29:08.640
got actually in

29:08.640 --> 29:09.260
the army, a

29:09.260 --> 29:09.840
secret briefing,

29:09.840 --> 29:11.100
was on the

29:11.100 --> 29:12.120
Russian nuclear

29:12.120 --> 29:13.340
threat in Europe

29:13.340 --> 29:14.400
at that time

29:14.400 --> 29:14.740
because I was

29:14.740 --> 29:15.400
going to go out

29:15.400 --> 29:16.640
and be what they

29:16.640 --> 29:17.240
call the covering

29:17.240 --> 29:17.540
force.

29:17.620 --> 29:18.600
We were literally

29:18.600 --> 29:19.760
the closest American

29:19.760 --> 29:21.360
forces on the

29:21.360 --> 29:23.100
border to confront

29:23.100 --> 29:23.980
the Soviet hordes.

29:24.020 --> 29:24.520
Now this was in

29:24.520 --> 29:26.340
1976, so we're

29:26.340 --> 29:27.300
talking eight years

29:27.300 --> 29:28.300
after the invasion

29:28.300 --> 29:29.200
of Czechoslovakia.

29:29.260 --> 29:29.720
So everything was

29:29.720 --> 29:30.400
very real and

29:30.400 --> 29:30.760
palpable.

29:31.260 --> 29:31.680
And the Germans

29:31.680 --> 29:32.480
were depending on

29:32.480 --> 29:34.500
us to defend them

29:34.500 --> 29:35.920
and the whole world

29:35.920 --> 29:36.720
in a sense.

29:37.260 --> 29:38.340
And part of that

29:38.340 --> 29:40.260
briefing was the

29:40.260 --> 29:41.120
idea that we had

29:41.120 --> 29:41.900
tactical nuclear

29:41.900 --> 29:42.720
weapons we would

29:42.720 --> 29:44.500
fire on them if

29:44.500 --> 29:46.400
they invaded.

29:46.640 --> 29:47.400
And I was a shock

29:47.400 --> 29:47.680
to me.

29:47.740 --> 29:48.440
That was my first

29:48.440 --> 29:49.260
introduction to

29:49.260 --> 29:50.560
nuclear weapons in a

29:50.560 --> 29:51.440
context of war,

29:52.040 --> 29:53.280
which nowadays when we

29:53.280 --> 29:54.420
listen to, where this

29:54.420 --> 29:55.020
would have gone full

29:55.020 --> 29:56.120
circle, we listen to

29:56.120 --> 29:57.220
Vladimir Putin talking

29:57.220 --> 29:58.260
about using nukes in

29:58.260 --> 29:59.600
Ukraine, we have to

29:59.600 --> 30:00.600
think about this idea

30:00.600 --> 30:01.980
of nuclear weapons.

30:02.100 --> 30:02.880
The tables have been

30:02.880 --> 30:03.760
reversed.

30:04.120 --> 30:05.180
Back then we needed

30:05.180 --> 30:06.820
them because we were

30:06.820 --> 30:07.380
afraid of being

30:07.380 --> 30:08.600
invaded and he's using

30:08.600 --> 30:09.180
them now what he

30:09.180 --> 30:10.120
regards to be if

30:10.120 --> 30:11.280
Russia's existence is

30:11.280 --> 30:12.760
threatened by NATO

30:12.760 --> 30:13.640
in the West, he would

30:13.640 --> 30:14.520
use them too, which is

30:14.520 --> 30:15.320
really what he said.

30:15.720 --> 30:16.760
So the point being at

30:16.760 --> 30:18.540
the time I'm in this

30:18.540 --> 30:20.140
kind of mode and my

30:20.140 --> 30:20.920
friends and I are all

30:20.920 --> 30:21.440
going through this

30:21.440 --> 30:22.280
together, the ones

30:22.280 --> 30:23.420
that, four of us,

30:23.420 --> 30:24.400
kind of the four

30:24.400 --> 30:24.880
horsemen of the

30:24.880 --> 30:25.280
apocalypse.

30:26.020 --> 30:28.460
And so I had this

30:28.460 --> 30:30.740
incredibly vivid dream

30:30.740 --> 30:32.600
in the midst of all

30:32.600 --> 30:33.900
this at Fort Knox

30:33.900 --> 30:36.040
where I dreamt that I

30:36.040 --> 30:37.320
was in a battle, like a

30:37.320 --> 30:38.320
battle of Armageddon.

30:38.940 --> 30:40.260
It's the first time the

30:40.260 --> 30:42.740
mystical things turned,

30:43.160 --> 30:44.380
I would call, turned

30:44.380 --> 30:45.880
religious or, you know,

30:45.980 --> 30:47.800
religious history when I

30:47.800 --> 30:49.120
became a big advocate or

30:49.120 --> 30:50.800
