42:00.940 --> 42:03.140
Now, that was in honor of two things I

42:03.140 --> 42:04.120
admired at the time.

42:04.300 --> 42:05.700
You know, you're, again, young, this is

42:05.700 --> 42:06.880
like typical of the way I was thinking

42:06.880 --> 42:07.480
at the time.

42:07.960 --> 42:09.640
Nietzsche, who was my favorite, Frederick

42:09.640 --> 42:11.280
Nietzsche, Friedrich Nietzsche, but, you

42:11.280 --> 42:13.780
know, Frederick, kind of adaptation of

42:13.780 --> 42:15.900
Nietzsche, who I'm obsessed, I was

42:15.900 --> 42:17.420
obsessed with, even at West Point, I go

42:17.420 --> 42:20.140
through some stories of Nietzsche, maybe

42:20.140 --> 42:21.720
because he fit this idea of, you know,

42:21.780 --> 42:23.120
to know yourself, you have to free

42:23.120 --> 42:23.480
yourself.

42:23.580 --> 42:25.520
You have to free, and even of God, you

42:25.520 --> 42:27.440
have to free yourself of all constraints

42:27.440 --> 42:30.180
on who you are and confront yourself as

42:30.180 --> 42:32.760
to who you are, which was also a theme

42:32.760 --> 42:34.760
at that time of a lot of the novels,

42:34.920 --> 42:36.300
fiction I like to read, particularly

42:36.300 --> 42:38.780
Hermann Hesse at the time in

42:38.780 --> 42:39.320
Steppenwolf.

42:39.760 --> 42:41.240
So the wolf came from that.

42:41.460 --> 42:43.500
Frederick Wolfe, ah, the man searching for

42:43.500 --> 42:44.760
his true nature, his true character.

42:44.760 --> 42:46.900
I'm willing to lay it all out there as

42:46.900 --> 42:50.080
a, you know, again, brask, brash guy.

42:50.560 --> 42:52.440
And so then I said, what would be my

42:52.440 --> 42:53.540
first short story?

42:54.240 --> 42:55.800
I'll write it here in this class.

42:56.240 --> 42:57.620
Well, I decided, I called it On

42:57.620 --> 42:59.200
Suicides, Suicide Note.

42:59.980 --> 43:01.680
Why did you choose that?

43:01.680 --> 43:03.720
Well, I thought it'd be, I chose it

43:03.720 --> 43:06.280
because it seemed like a really dark,

43:06.500 --> 43:08.300
deep theme to write about it.

43:08.320 --> 43:10.160
So I imagine the note was the note I

43:10.160 --> 43:11.360
would leave if I actually committed

43:11.360 --> 43:11.780
suicide.

43:11.780 --> 43:14.680
So it was like, if I left a note now

43:14.680 --> 43:16.660
because I don't, you know, I don't want

43:16.660 --> 43:19.140
to encourage this thinking, anybody out

43:19.140 --> 43:22.120
there, and it came to my senses, so to

43:22.120 --> 43:23.500
speak, but I was getting into the

43:23.500 --> 43:24.080
novelistic.

43:24.300 --> 43:25.900
In fact, the irony was I've never in my

43:25.900 --> 43:27.340
life felt in the slightest bit suicidal

43:27.340 --> 43:28.080
ever, ever.

43:28.880 --> 43:31.240
And I attribute a lot of that to my faith

43:31.240 --> 43:33.640
and belief because I'm also an

43:33.640 --> 43:36.740
inveterate optimist, even in the future

43:36.740 --> 43:37.080
of the world.

43:37.120 --> 43:38.540
Even with all the dark things I've

43:38.540 --> 43:41.080
talked about, war and apocalypse and

43:41.080 --> 43:43.040
Armageddon, and I'm actually very

43:43.040 --> 43:44.720
optimistic about it because it's all

43:44.720 --> 43:46.340
tied to this God I know is a loving

43:46.340 --> 43:46.760
God.

43:47.960 --> 43:50.820
This God is the creator God, means

43:50.820 --> 43:52.100
everything around you in nature, you

43:52.100 --> 43:53.780
can see God and how wonderful it is.

43:54.220 --> 43:56.060
It's this personal God you can talk and

43:56.060 --> 43:57.960
interact with who loves you, who wants

43:57.960 --> 43:58.640
you to love him.

43:59.920 --> 44:02.280
So how can you not be an optimist if

44:02.280 --> 44:03.080
that's your perspective?

44:03.460 --> 44:05.040
So I had that perspective, even that,

44:05.040 --> 44:06.160
because I hadn't forgotten the

44:06.160 --> 44:08.980
childhood things in my life that made

44:08.980 --> 44:09.820
me feel that way.

44:10.080 --> 44:11.760
But I'm going to go down this dark

44:11.760 --> 44:12.940
road because it's interesting.

44:13.180 --> 44:15.080
And one of my inspirations was Camus,

44:15.240 --> 44:17.820
the philosopher, who was obsessed by

44:17.820 --> 44:20.360
the question and mused that maybe the

44:20.360 --> 44:22.420
only really relevant question to think

44:22.420 --> 44:24.760
about was, is life worth living?

44:25.000 --> 44:27.100
Because you have complete control of

44:27.100 --> 44:31.940
your life from that very basic way of

44:31.940 --> 44:32.660
looking at it.

44:32.660 --> 44:34.740
And I, and I, so I wrote this thing

44:34.740 --> 44:37.260
and, and that's when I had these

44:37.260 --> 44:39.940
dreams, uh, you know, and, and at that

44:39.940 --> 44:41.380
same time, this is all happening

44:41.380 --> 44:43.020
concurrent with what I've talked about.

44:43.140 --> 44:44.880
So I realized I was getting in way too

44:44.880 --> 44:46.360
dark, way too deep.

44:46.660 --> 44:48.320
It was, and then the dreams were

44:48.320 --> 44:50.740
exacerbating my, my thinking again,

44:50.740 --> 44:53.460
never got negative or self-destructive.

44:53.460 --> 44:54.740
That's the funny part.

44:55.220 --> 44:56.860
And I'm convinced I could have kept

44:56.860 --> 44:59.700
plowing down that deeper, deep, that

44:59.700 --> 45:01.740
tunnel deeper and deeper without ever

45:01.740 --> 45:04.120
hurting myself or any, anybody or

45:04.120 --> 45:05.720
anything, but that's not necessarily

45:05.720 --> 45:07.640
for other people, something I would

45:07.640 --> 45:08.100
advise.

45:08.100 --> 45:08.440
Right.

45:08.980 --> 45:11.480
Uh, but it all culminated in, in the

45:11.480 --> 45:14.220
next day I saw, I gotta clear my head.

45:14.280 --> 45:15.100
Let's go play golf.

45:15.180 --> 45:16.700
So we were all terrible golfers, but

45:16.700 --> 45:18.520
we like to go hacking at golf at, at

45:18.520 --> 45:21.100
Fort Knox, they have military golf course

45:21.100 --> 45:22.040
